Definition.WordDefinition: Mammary \Mam"ma*ry\, a. [Cf. F. mammaire.] (Anat.) Of or pertaining to the mamm[ae] or breasts; as, the mammary arteries and veins. [1913 Webster]
mammary adj : of or relating to the milk-giving gland of the female
